  "prompt": "How do I filter out US election news in my Quora feed?",
  "response": "To filter out US election news in your Quora feed, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Adjust Your Settings**: Go to your Quora account settings. Look for options related to interests or topics you follow. You might find a way to unfollow specific topics related to US elections.\n\n2. **Manage Your Following**: If you follow topics or spaces that frequently post about US elections, consider unfollowing them. Instead, you can focus on topics that interest you and are unrelated to elections.\n\n3. **Use the \"Hide\" Feature**: When you see a post about US elections in your feed, you can click on the three dots (options menu) on the post and select \"Hide this post.\" This helps train the algorithm not to show you similar content in the future.\n\n4. **Provide Feedback**: Quora often allows users to provide feedback on content they see. If you have the option, indicate that you\u2019re not interested in election-related content.\n\n5. **Browse Selectively**: When searching for content, use specific keywords to find questions and topics unrelated to US elections, and engage with that content to help guide the algorithm.\n\nBy applying these strategies, you can help customize your Quora feed to better match your interests.",
